sec.p:
The following standardized methods of bacteriology procedures were used, according to standards in force:
SR EN ISO 21528-2/2007, Microbiology of food and animal feeding stuffs—Horizontal methods for the detection and enumeration of Enterobacteriaceae—Part 2: Colony-count method—E. coli;
SR EN ISO 7932/2005, Horizontal method for the enumeration of presumptive B. cereus—Colony-count technique at 30 °C;
SR EN ISO 6579/2003/AC/2004/AC/2006, 2007, Horizontal method for detection of bacteria of the genus Salmonella spp;
